name: PLATO FILIPINO
address: PLATO FILIPINO, 5175 Joyce St, Vancouver, BC V5R 4G8

featured_reviews.review_id: I have no idea why this place is rated 4 stars. So surprised with what I was given because usually Filipino food is good. I don't know if I was given the leftovers or what. The pork in the sinigang was SO dry, I had a tough time chewing it. The bbq was super dry as well. Look at these portions compared to my hand. My hand is the size of a child's hand and I wear XS Gloves. This was a "regular" size soup. Super disappointed!

featured_reviews.review_id:
Plato Filipino takes me back home with their authentic Filpino dishes. Name your favorite dish and they have it!

I commend not only their appetizing food but also their great customer service. The front staff are nice and helpful.

I recommend their Combo Special where you can choose any two dishes and a cup of rice. My husband loved their Lechon Kawali, Buko Pandan and Leche Flan. Yes, they have a variety of desserts as well! So many to choose from so we always make sure to order takeout.

We will surely go back again.

featured_reviews.review_id:
I ordered from Uber recently and what I ordered was all large sizes that cost $17.99. When I received my order the containers that I received was the small sizes. I called them and they didn't do anything to compensate us. So be aware when ordering from Uber, Skip or Dash, this restaurant will fool you and take advantage of you. Also, I order beef tendon nilaga and its all tendons without any vegetable. I know  that nilaga recipe has some vegetable at least with bokchoy, potato and green beans. This is a $17.99 charge.

So don't be fooled. Be aware of PLATO FILIPINO.

featured_reviews.response_from_owner_text:
Hi Ms. Tonet, thank you for taking time to write your thoughts about Plato Filipino. Online platforms are setting a commission on restaurants which is we are no control of. Fooling our customers is and will never be a thought. 
We sincerely apologize, however, on your order on the lack of vegetables, we will look into this appropriately, thank you for calling our attention, very much appreciated. Take care.

featured_reviews.review_id: Plato Filipino will always get 5 stars from me. I am fortunate to have this location only a few minutes walk from my house. I've also visited their other location in New Westminster. The food is always delicious, and no matter what I order, be it a combo meal or one from their a la carte, I am always satisfied! Servers are also excellent, and they are always efficient, happy, and polite. I can't wait to go back and would recommend it to anyone looking for a Filipino Restau to eat in. Truly a taste of home away from home

featured_reviews.review_id: not sure what happened. new owners? or just inflation? used to be good food with decent portions. now it's very small portions. and isn't nearly as tasty as it used to be. you might get one piece of meat in your Kaldereta. thought it was just a bad day, but went back a few times since and same thing. it's a shame, I loved this place before.

featured_reviews.review_id:
This place is a classic Filipino restaurant serving authentic and traditional Filipino dishes with many choices. The foods are outstanding at a reasonable price. One of my favorites is their signature dish "Crispy Pata" which I always order for takeout. Very crispy and cooked to perfection which is completely paired with their signature vinegar dipping sauce. They also serve various desserts such as halo-halo (sweet shaved ice dessert with various toppings), Turon ( sweet banana-jackfruit spring roll), Buko Pandan (coconut and pandan flavored gelatin with cream and sweetened milk), and a lot more.

The place also features decor and ambiance, reflecting Filipino culture with Filipino music playing in the background. Plus, they have a very friendly, welcoming, and pretty staff. This is a must-try restaurant that tastes like Home. If you miss Pinoy foods or want to try authentic Filipino cuisine, this place is for you.
